722473f-a.title: Manhattan: Patchin Place - 10th Street (West)
722473f-a.text:
(1)
Patchin Place, on the north side of West 10th Street, between
Sixth and Greenwich Aves., showing a small dead end alley. This view
shows only Nos. 1 to 9 which are on the east side of this quaint,
forgotten street.
August 20, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The gate which Was erected later. Photographers vantage point is
on West 10th Street.
September 18, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

722475f.title: Manhattan: Patchin Place - 10th Street (West)
722475f.text:
Patchin Place, north from W. 10th Street.
1938-9
Alexander Alland
NO REPRODU1TIONS
This photo is one of a series that appeared in the published volume

722471f-a.title: Manhattan: Patchin Place - 10th Street
722471f-a.text:
Patchin Place, north from 10th (formerly Amos) Street, west of
Sixth Avenue, showing the entire length of this little alley.
Around 1921 the old houses were remodelled and the place painted up
to attract the ''Villager'' type of young people who like picturesdue
housing with low rents.
June, 1925.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
